*****
[2] Brazil
Date: Sat 7 May 2022
Source: Play Crazy Game [edited]
https://playcrazygame.com/2022/05/07/first-suspected-case-of-hepatitis-in-brazil-is-a-3-year-old-child/


A week ago, the first suspected case of hepatitis of unknown cause was reported in a child in Brazil. According to an investigation by the newspaper O GLOBO, the Ministry of Health stated that the registration took place in Niterói, Rio de Janeiro. In all, the country is investigating 7 suspected cases of the disease; 1 of the children needed a liver transplant. On [Thu 5 May 2022], Argentina confirmed the 1st case in Latin America, in an 8-year-old child.

The World Health Organization (WHO) regards the situation as a "very urgent" issue and said it is giving "absolute priority" to it.

[Byline: Jenni Smith]

